â€œThe Crowd Woke the Whistleâ€ â€“ A Satirical Stanza 
Musovski saw red, the ref saw none, Till the crowd rose up like a loaded gun. Their voices cracked the evening air, And suddenly Puebla had fouls to spare. A trip, a tug, a shirt pulled tightâ€” Now the whistle sang through the night. Too late, too loud, too full of spin, Justice arrivedâ€”but not to win, but justice took place when the kicks kicked in. (CopyRight LDP)

comments.author: @LDP-i5n
comments.text:
â€œThe Keeperâ€™s Creedâ€ â€“ A Tribute to Andrew Thomas
When chaos reigned and tempers flared, And Musovskiâ€™s boots were prematurely spared, The crowd grew loud, the ref grew blind, But Thomas kept a sharper mind.
Ten men stood where eleven fell, In Pueblaâ€™s storm, a Sounders shell. Yet through the din and penalty haze, one keeper rose to steal the praise.
A dive to left, a stretch to right, He turned despair into delight. Two saves, like thunder split the skyâ€” A calm defiance in each eye.
No cape, no crown, no scripted fame, just gloves and grit and love for game. He placed the Sounders in their lane and sent Club Puebla home in pain. (CopyRight LDP)

The Sounders have gotten it all together, But you can't handle an opposing team with 12 members. One wears stripes and wields the whistleâ€™s power, Turns fair play sour by the minute, by the hour.
They pass, they press, they play with flair, While refs invent fouls from thin air. A phantom trip, a glance too boldâ€” Out comes the card, the drama unfolds.
